-- Pentagon Creates ‘Special Victims Units’ to Curb Sexual Assault
-- B y   D a v i d   L e r m a n
-- 2012-04-16T21:47:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-16/pentagon-creates-special-victims-units-to-curb-sexual-assault.html
Defense Secretary  Leon Panetta  said
the U.S. military is creating a “special victims unit” in each
service branch as part of a new effort to curb sexual assaults.  Trained investigators, prosecutors and assistance personnel
in the units will collect evidence and assist victims of
assault, according to a Defense Department statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Lerman in Washington at 
 dlerman1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
